    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - 10 SPEED AND 15 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RT, RTO, AND RTX
        SERIES - REMOVE - AUXILIARY DRIVE GEAR
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="4">
        <title>AUXILIARY DRIVE GEAR</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1301564">Figure 64</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1301564" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1301564" filename="../figg13/G1301564.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 64. Auxiliary Drive Gear Exploded View</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the snap ring from the mainshaft rear groove (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301565">Figure 65</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301565" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301565" filename="../figg13/G1301565.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 65. Remove Snap Ring From Mainshaft Rear Groove</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Cut the lockwire and remove the bolts from the bearing retainer ring (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301566">Figure 66</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301566" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301566" filename="../figg13/G1301566.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 66. Cut Lockwire and Remove Bolts From Bearing Retainer Ring</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Insert three bolts in the specially tapped holes of the retainer ring (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301567">Figure 67</hotlnk>). Tighten bolts evenly to pull the auxiliary drive gear
                assembly from the case bore.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301567" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301567" filename="../figg13/G1301567.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 67. Insert Bolts in Retainer Ring Holes</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
